title: monitor mode
link: http://books.gigatux.nl/mirror/networksecuritytools/0596007949/networkst-CHP-10-SECT-3.html
tag: wireless, monitor
status: none
summary: 
Driver/card   Command
Cisco Aironet   Echo "mode: y" > '/proc/driver/aironet/<device>/Config'
HostAP          iwconfig <device> mode monitor
Orinoco (patched)     iwpriv <device> monitor 1 <channel>
Madwifi         iwconfig <device> mode monitor
Wlan-ng         wlanctl-ng <device> lnxreq_wlansniff channel=<channel> enable=true
Radiotap        ifconfig <device> monitor up | custom command
linux-wlan-ng project (http://www.linux-wlan.com/)
ftp://ftp.linux-wlan.org/pub/linux-wlan-ng/
